---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
---
<Base title="Leaves.PH · Metro Manila canopy report" pathname="/">
  <!-- KICKER + HEADLINE -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 pt-12 pb-4">
    <p class="kicker mb-6">REPORT &middot; {today} &middot; NATIONAL CAPITAL REGION</p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-editorial gap-x-12 gap-y-6 items-end">
      <h1 class="font-display font-medium tracking-tight text-ink-900 leading-[0.95]" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);">
        Metro Manila's tree cover, finally measured.
      </h1>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="kicker text-ink-500">THE FIVE NUMBERS</p>
        <dl class="text-sm font-mono space-y-1.5 tabular-nums leading-relaxed">
          <div class="flex justify-between"><dt>DENR FMB cited</dt><dd>6.00<span class="text-ink-300">%</span> <span class="tag-disputed ml-1">unsourced</span></dd></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><dt>GFW dashboard</dt><dd>4.00<span class="text-ink-300">%</span> <span class="tag-disputed ml-1">understates</span></dd></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><dt>EJN open forest</dt><dd>2,071 ha <span class="tag-unverified ml-1">def. mismatch</span></dd></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><dt>ScienceKonek 2024</dt><dd>n/a <span class="tag-unverified ml-1">not findable</span></dd></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between text-ink-900"><dt>Meta v2 truth (&gt;5m)</dt><dd>7.50<span class="text-ink-300">%</span> <span class="tag-verified ml-1">independent</span></dd></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between text-forest-700 font-medium pt-1 border-t border-ink-900"><dt>LEAVES.PH 2026</dt><dd>7.46<span class="text-forest-300">%</span> <span class="tag-verified ml-1">reproducible</span></dd></div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TIME-ANIMATED HERO -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 pb-12">
    <figure class="border border-ink-900 bg-paper">
      <img
        src="/demo/remaining-canopy-timeline.gif"
        alt="Editorial map of remaining tree cover in Metro Manila, 2019 to 2026. Per-pixel canopy density at 30 m drawn over LGU outlines on a paper basemap. Densest cover concentrates in the NE around Quezon City and the La Mesa watershed; sparse elsewhere."
        class="block w-full h-auto"
        loading="eager"
      />
      <figcaption class="fig-caption px-4 py-3 border-t border-ink-900 bg-paper-tint flex flex-wrap justify-between gap-2">
        <span>FIG&nbsp;1 &middot; REMAINING TREE COVER &middot; NCR &middot; 2019 to 2026 (8 frames)</span>
        <span>Pixel: 30 m &middot; Source: Sentinel-2 NDVI &ge; 0.62 against Meta v2</span>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <!-- LEDE -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 pb-12 grid md:grid-cols-editorial-wide gap-x-16 gap-y-8">
    <div class="max-w-prose">
      <p class="dropcap text-lg leading-[1.7] text-ink-700 mb-6">
        When the May 2026 RadarPH post and the news cycle that followed declared "Metro Manila is rapidly becoming a city without trees", four different sources had been quoted for the headline canopy number. The four disagreed by half.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.7] text-ink-700 mb-6">
        Leaves.PH publishes a fifth measurement, taken from fresh 2026 Sentinel-2 imagery, calibrated against Meta's 1 m AI canopy height, aggregated against the 17 NCR LGU polygons, hash-verified for bit-exact reproducibility. The whole pipeline is in the open: <code>make fetch &amp;&amp; make compute &amp;&amp; make verify</code>.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.7] text-ink-700">
        The number is 7.46 percent. It validates DENR's cited 6 percent (within methodology variance). It refutes Global Forest Watch's published 4.0 percent (which understates 2026 by 3.46 percentage points). It is within 0.04 percentage points of Meta's independent ground-truth measurement. <a href="/map" class="no-underline text-forest-700">Explore the map &nbsp;&rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="border-t border-ink-900 pt-4">
      <p class="kicker text-ink-500 mb-4">FIG&nbsp;1 &middot; PER-LGU CANOPY 2026</p>
      <table class="w-full text-xs font-mono tabular-nums">
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-ink-300/50">
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-900">Quezon City</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">18.93%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-900">Mandaluyong</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">11.19%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-900">Makati</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">8.92%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-900">Caloocan</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">8.80%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-900">Marikina</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">6.87%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">Taguig</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">6.47%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">Valenzuela</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">5.81%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">Pasig</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">5.23%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">Las Pinas</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">5.20%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">Pateros</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">4.96%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">Paranaque</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">4.35%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">Muntinlupa</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">3.77%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">Malabon</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">3.68%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">San Juan</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">2.41%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-500">Pasay</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">2.08%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-900">Manila</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">0.89%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1.5 text-ink-900">Navotas</td><td class="py-1.5 text-right">0.47%</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="fig-caption">Source: Leaves.PH 2026, Sentinel-2 NDVI &ge; 0.62 against Meta canopy height v2 ground-truth, aggregated against OSM admin_level=6 polygons.</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule max-w-6xl mx-auto" />

  <!-- PULL QUOTE / FINDING -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 py-8">
    <p class="kicker text-ink-500 mb-3">FINDING</p>
    <blockquote class="pullquote not-italic font-display">
      &ldquo;Global Forest Watch's published 4.0 percent figure materially understates Metro Manila's 2026 canopy. DENR's cited 6 percent is closer to but slightly below the satellite-validated 7.5 percent.&rdquo;
    </blockquote>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule max-w-6xl mx-auto" />

  <!-- METHOD AT-A-GLANCE -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 py-8 grid md:grid-cols-editorial-wide gap-x-16 gap-y-6">
    <div class="max-w-prose">
      <p class="kicker text-ink-500 mb-3">METHOD</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl mb-4 text-ink-900">Five canonical layers, one threshold tuned against a 1 m truth raster.</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.7] text-ink-700">
        Sentinel-2 L2A median composites (cloud-masked at s2cloudless probability &lt; 40, 30 m); Hansen Global Forest Change v1.13 for the loss-year band back to 2001; ESA WorldCover v200 (2021) as an independent cross-check; Dynamic World v1 for fuzzy probability; Meta Canopy Height v2 (1 m, 2018-2020 imagery) as the calibration truth.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        <a href="/methodology" class="no-underline text-forest-700">Full methodology &rarr;</a>
        &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
        <a href="/data" class="no-underline text-forest-700">Data downloads &rarr;</a>
        &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
        <a href="https://github.com/xmpuspus/leaves-ph" class="no-underline text-forest-700">GitHub &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="border-l border-ink-900 pl-6 space-y-4 max-w-narrow">
      <div>
        <p class="kicker text-ink-500">RESOLUTION</p>
        <p class="font-display text-2xl text-ink-900 leading-tight">1 m height truth &middot; 30 m time series &middot; 17 LGUs</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="kicker text-ink-500">PROVENANCE</p>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700">Every input is canonical public satellite. Every threshold is committed. Every number on this page traces back to a script in the repository.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="kicker text-ink-500">LICENSE</p>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700">Code MIT. Data CC-BY-4.0. Cite as: Leaves.PH (YYYY-Q-N).</p>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule max-w-6xl mx-auto" />

  <!-- THE MAP TEASE -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 py-8">
    <p class="kicker text-ink-500 mb-3">THE MAP</p>
    <a href="/map" class="block group no-underline">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-editorial gap-x-12 gap-y-4 items-end">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-display-2 text-ink-900 mb-3 group-hover:text-forest-700 transition-colors">
            Every canopy patch above 5 m, mapped per LGU, year by year.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-base leading-[1.7] text-ink-700 max-w-prose">
            Click any LGU to see its 2019 to 2026 curve, Hansen cumulative loss, and the ESA 2021 cross-check. Year slider drives the choropleth. Tree-crown polygons load at street zoom.
          </p>
        </div>
        <p class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-700 underline group-hover:text-forest-700">open the interactive map &rarr;</p>
      </div>
    </a>
  </section>
</Base>
